## Rules

### BACK-001: Error Wrapping
severity: ERROR
scope: all Go functions returning error
rule: All errors MUST be wrapped with context using `fmt.Errorf("context: %w", err)`. Ignoring errors with `_` is prohibited except for Close() calls in defer statements. Every error path MUST be tested.
threshold: max_function_lines=40, max_complexity=10
example_correct: |
  user, err := repo.FindByID(ctx, id)
  if err != nil {
      return nil, fmt.Errorf("get user %d: %w", id, err)
  }
example_incorrect: |
  user, _ := repo.FindByID(ctx, id)  // error ignored — prohibited

### BACK-002: Context Propagation
severity: ERROR
scope: all Go service and repository functions
rule: All I/O-bound functions MUST accept `context.Context` as their first parameter. Context values MUST NOT be stored in structs. goroutines MUST respect context cancellation.
threshold: max_function_lines=40
example_correct: |
  func (r *UserRepo) FindByID(ctx context.Context, id int64) (*User, error) { ... }
example_incorrect: |
  type Repo struct { ctx context.Context }  // stored context — prohibited
